data.description: Located in the heart of Western Colorado, this residence offers a unique opportunity to embrace the serene beauty of the region, with breathtaking views of the majestic Grand Mesa.  This four-bedroom/two-bath home sits on just under a half-acre.  The gally-style kitchen leads into the dining/living room area.  The cozy rock fireplace, with an electric insert, provides a comfortable sitting area perfect for chilly nights.  The landscaping is Xeriscaped and graveled for low-maintenance living and conservation of water. There is a large double-lofted shed for additional storage.  On the North side of the property, there is 50-amp service for an RV and 220 power.   On the West side of the property, the views encompass the unparalleled beauty of Western Colorado living with views of the Grand Mesa and the Adobes.      The roof was replaced in September 2023, knocking out a significant expense!   All appliances are less than three years old. The attached spacious garage provides adequate area for woodworking, car hobbies, and parking.
